and they said to each other that they wanted to be at the sea.
Rato puserek , faat nra nen rato puserek panpan go §
046-003 rakaitmer nrikir ki na ramuur rakfan pato elau .
And the small stone said to the big stone, "You go first.
§ 046-004 Go faat sees inrik faat p̃ur ki na , " Ag p̃afei .
And they ended up arguing with each other
until the the big rock said to the small one,
046-007 panpan go faat p̃ur inrik faat , faat sees ki na §
"You go first down there, I will stone you and we will go in the ocean,
that people paddle out to, we will be in the middle.
046-008 " Ag p̃afei , p̃afei pan pato etan , me neu kafo neetnpasilkik me takfo
pan pato namos , § 046-009 nen natam̃ol ruto palus , akit tato maloput ".
The small rock told the big rock, "You go first and I will follow."
§ 046-011 Faat sees inrik faat p̃ur ki na , " E , ag p̃afei me kineu kafo inrok ."
And the big rock said, "You are small, but I am big.
§ 046-012 Go faat p̃ur inrikin ki na , " Ag kusees , me kineu atop .
When you go first, I'll follow and I'll stone you and we will go."
§ 046-013 Malen kin ag p̃afei pa , neu kafei , kainrok na kanpasilkik go takfo pa ."
They kept arguing. Until the small rock said, "Alright, I will go first."
§ 046-014 Rapreg ipi nafsaplilwen . Panpan go faat sees
And the small stone stayed up high, it rolled down.
§ 046-015 Go elag , imlil faat mai to sees etan ito .
The big rock wanted to come, it couldn't stone him.
§ 046-016 Faat p̃ur ina imai ikano npasilki .
And they are still there until today.
§ 046-017 nen rato euut to to pan tup̃ Go mees mees .
It is only a short story.
